-height:115%;\r\n mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n font-size:11.0pt;\r\n font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";\r\n mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;\r\n mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\n mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;\r\n mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\n mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";\r\n mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;}\r\n&lt;/style&gt;\r\n&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;!--[if gte mso 9]>&lt;xml&gt;\r\n <o v:ext="edit" spidmax="1026"></o>\r\n&lt;/xml&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;!--[if gte mso 9]>&lt;xml&gt;\r\n <o v:ext="edit">\r\n  <o v:ext="edit" data="1"></o>\r\n </o>&lt;/xml&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b xss=removed><u><span xss=removed>Strengths of curriculum for the subject of Pathology:</span></u></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>i.<span xss=removed>                  \r\n</span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Pathology\r\nis a bridging discipline between basic and clinical subjects. Students must\r\nhave to know the pathology and pathogenesis of any disease. This pathology\r\ncurriculum explains basic mechanism of diseases very effectively.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>ii.<span xss=removed>               \r\n</span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>This\r\ncurriculum correlates well between clinical findings and pathological changes.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>iii.<span xss=removed>            \r\n</span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>This\r\ncurriculum emphasizes on different diseases and tumour of the body. Their causes,\r\nrisk factors, mechanism of formation and diagnosis.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>iv.<span xss=removed>              \r\n</span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>This\r\ncurriculum brings the ability of the students to think about investigation plan\r\nfor diagnosis and follow up of diseases.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>v.<span xss=removed>                 \r\n</span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>It\r\nhelps students developing knowledge about the use of Histopathology, FNAC,\r\nCytological examination, Pap smear, Frozen section and Immuno-histochemistry.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>vi.<span xss=removed>              \r\n</span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>By\r\nfollowing this curriculum students will be able to interpret laboratory results\r\nand understand their implication.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b xss=removed><u><span xss=removed>Weaknesses of curriculum for the subject of Pathology:</span></u></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>i.<span xss=removed>                   \r\n</span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>The curriculum is very vast but time period for implementation\r\nis very short. Only around seven months to complete the full syllabus.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>ii.<span xss=removed>               </span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Very less scope for practical procedure classes as there are\r\naround 69 items to cover in this short time duration. The practical classes\r\nhave to be converted into tutorial or lecture classes to complete the items. So\r\nhere is less scope for the laboratory diagnosis part of pathology subject.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>iii.<span xss=removed>             </span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Hematology and clinical pathology was a separate card in\r\nprevious curriculum. In this 2012 curriculum hematology and clinical pathology\r\nhas been merged with systemic pathology. For this there is less time and scope\r\nfor the teachers to take classes on this two important system which is very\r\nimportant for clinical practice.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>iv.<span xss=removed>               \r\n</span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Systemic pathology syllabus includes almost every disease\r\nincluding tumours of various organ system. In the undergraduate level it could\r\nbe reduced to basic and common diseases and tumours bearing in mind that there\r\nare other two important subject pharmacology and microbiology to cover in this\r\nsame duration.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>v.<span xss=removed>                 \r\n</span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>This curriculum is clinically oriented with organ based disease\r\nstudy. But this curriculum is studied in 4<sup>th</sup> year where students\r\nhave to attend clinical ward from 3<sup>rd</sup> year. So it is difficult for\r\nthem to understand like “what is inflammation” in the 3<sup>rd</sup> year\r\nbecause pathology classes are started from 4<sup>th</sup> year.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>vi.<span xss=removed>              </span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>There is limited scope for problem based questions in this\r\ncurriculum. Problem based questions now a days is a very important tool for\r\nassessing a students ability. The percentage of problem based question in both\r\nwritten and viva examination is low. </span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b xss=removed><u><span xss=removed>Discussion about improvement of the curriculum of Pathology:</span></u></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>i.<span xss=removed>                 </span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>To cover the whole syllabus pathology classes (at least one per\r\nweek) can be started from 3<sup>rd</sup> year so that teachers get adequate\r\ntime for discussing every points identified in the curriculum. Moreover,\r\nstudents starts clinical bed side teaching from 3<sup>rd</sup> year, so topics\r\non general pathology like inflammation, tumour can be covered by 3<sup>rd</sup>\r\nyear classes.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>ii.<span xss=removed>               </span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Elaborating general pathology and shortening systemic pathology syllabus\r\ncan be done as general pathology is very important for understanding the basic\r\nmechanism of the diseases. This current curriculum gives emphasis on systemic\r\npathology more which can be reduced to lower the huge syllabus burden and time\r\nshortage.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>iii.<span xss=removed>               \r\n</span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Hematology and clinical pathology part has less share in this\r\ncurriculum which can be increased. Hematology and clinical pathology is an\r\nimportant part of clinical practice and diagnosis of disease. </span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>iv.<span xss=removed>               \r\n</span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>There is about 69 items to complete in this curriculum, which is\r\nhuge in respect of time allocated to complete the syllabus. Item numbers can be\r\nlowered to cover syllabus smoothly in time.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b xss=removed><u><span xss=removed>Implementation of the curriculum in my own situation:</span></u></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>i.<span xss=removed>                </span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>As the syllabus is vast for the time duration given for\r\nimplementation, lecture classes should be specific and examination oriented.\r\nMoreover, there is a lot of items to be completed so there may be no scope for\r\nthe lecturers to give tutorial on that topic. So everything important and\r\ninstructed to the curriculum should be covered in the lecture classes.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>ii.<span xss=removed>              </span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Practical procedures and laboratory practical classes must have\r\nto be taken according to the curriculum as laboratory diagnosis is an important\r\npart of pathology learning. Even there is a item schedule in a practical class,\r\natleast 30 minutes practical class should be taken before taking items.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>iii.<span xss=removed>              </span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>The lecturers should be trained and instructed according to the\r\ncurriculum so that they can take items specifically on the topic and cover\r\nimportant questions asked in the viva examination.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>iv.<span xss=removed>              </span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed></span>Problem based questions\r\nshould be developed and discussed more with the students to build their\r\nclinical eye. These problem based questions should be included more in the\r\nwritten and in viva examination.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>v.<span xss=removed>               </span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Students can be asked to see directly the FNAC and\r\nHistopathology procedures to increase their knowledge regarding disease\r\nconditions and tumorous conditions of the body.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>vi.<span xss=removed>             </span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>The importance of the subject both for passing examination and\r\nalso for knowing about the disease process should be clearly stated to the\r\nstudents. Students should be motivated and encouraged by the professors and\r\nlecturers to study pathology. Items and assessment examinations must be taken\r\nin time and in standard procedure.</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p>', '2018-01-20 00:54:18', 'upload/attachment/5b0ca3349a1619d7b34af8b326771ded.docx', '<p>a) The strength and weakness of the existing curriculum could have been discussed in the light of 10 points</p><p>b) From a vast contents of pathology, a must know portion could be identified to emphasize<br></p><p>c) Suggestions on how to improve could have been grouped</p><p>d) Ways of implementation could be specific<br></p>', NULL, '2018-01-20 06:54:18', NULL),
(9, 15, 'Evaluation of our MBBS curriculum on Anatomy. Identification of its strengths and weaknesses. Suggestions how to improve and implement the curriculum.', '<p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Strengths :<o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>1. Well organised.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>2. Structured.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>3. Systematic delivery of content by the teaching stuff.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>4. Specific content.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>4. Specific aims and objectives to acheive the goal.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>5. Outcome base education.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>6. Formative assesment.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>7.Summative assesment.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>7. Comprehensive<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>8. Multiple choice question (MCQ)  in written examination.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>9.  Short answered\r\nquestion (SAQ) instead of long question in written examination.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>10.Inclusion of radiology and imaging oriented anatomy study\r\nand assesment. <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>11.Inclusion of surface anatomy oriented anatomy study and  assesment.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>12. Inclusion of OSPE in practical examination.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>13. Proper sequence of implementation to obtain the aims and\r\nobjectives<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>14. Series of planned activies for specific learning outcome.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>15.Constant monitoing, examination (item,card and term),\r\nevaluation, assesment by the teaching staff.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>16. Small group teaching making the curriculum both student\r\nand teacher centered.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>17. Specifying the curriculum into core content and learning\r\nobjectives. <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>17. well ordered in delivery of component for better learning\r\noutcome.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>18. lecture integrated teaching.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>19. Inclusion of tutorial, practical and demonstration\r\noriented teaching method.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><o> </o></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Weaknesses:<o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>1. In multiple choice question (MCQ) making core curriculum\r\npartially followed.<b><o></o></b></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>2. Questions repeat while preparing multiple choice question and\r\nshort answered question. <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>2. Partially integrated.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>3. Allocated time in order to content is not enough.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>4. Overloaded with examination in order to allocated time.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>5. Relatively less emphasis on clinical oriented anatomy\r\nstudy and assesment.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>6. Clinical part of any Anatomy topic teaching not practical\r\noriented.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>7. Teaching part is not integrated among Anatomy, Physiology\r\nand Biochemistry <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>8. No specific standard, allocation of resources.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>9. No specific standard about educational environment.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>10. Not task oriented.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>11. More teacher centered.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>12. Inclusion of some contents which are usually regarded to\r\nbe of higher level of difficulty e.g . some topic of genetics and nervous\r\nsystem.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><o> </o></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Suggestion  For \r\nImprovement :<o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>1.Task based and problem based teaching should be practiced\r\nmore.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>2. Integrated teaching should be more practiced among\r\nanatomy, physiology and biochemistry.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>3. Resources should be adressed specifically.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>4. Oral examination should be more structured but more flexible\r\nin order to interact with the examinee to facilate her response.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>5.Core content should be more specific in the field of hard\r\ncore, soft core and optional core content.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>6. Time allocation for radiology imaging and surface anatomy\r\nshould be more.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>7. Teaching stuff should be more specific about the\r\nreferences of book<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>8. Evaluation of curriculum by students and teachers may be\r\nfurther analyzed<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>and taken under consideration to upgrade the curriculum.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>9. Curriculum should be more student centered.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>10. Educational environment should be more consensus.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>11. Modification of teaching learning method with more\r\nemphasis on practical examintation.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>12. Some topic and hour from Community medicine should be reduced\r\nand allocated those time to anatomy subject.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>13. Every content should have more specific teaching\r\nmethod  and during  small group \r\nteaching,  application of this\r\nspecific method to all group should be mendatory.  <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed> 14. Simplistic veiw of\r\ncurriculum planning keeping in mind the real challenges of  medical educaton.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>15. Assesment should be developed in parallel with the other\r\naspect of curriculum.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>16.The process of evaluation should be done with the veiws of\r\nstudents, teachers and administrative staff and then should take rapid\r\nintervention and correction of faults.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>17. More emphasis should given on spiral curriculum so that\r\nstudents find more integrated curriculum throughout their course of study.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>  18. Identification of core knowledge that all\r\nstudents need to learn and should occupy two third of the curriculum.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>19. Staff should be appointed with particular expertise in\r\ncurriculum planning, teaching methods and assesment to suport work on the\r\ncurriculum.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>20. Frequent and continous monitoring in the implementations\r\nof all domains of curriculum and that monitoring should be done by undergraduate\r\nmedical education commitee.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>21.Use of study guide and curriculum map by the teaching\r\nstaffs as a method of communication with the students.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed><o> </o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Implementation:<o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>1. Evaluation of curriculum through questionnair to make out\r\nviews of students and   teachers involved\r\nin anatomy teaching.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>2. Integrated teaching should be more implementated.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>3. More emphasis on interprofessional teaching where students\r\nlook at a subject  from the perspective\r\nof other professionals as well as their owns.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>4.Communication between teachers and students to bring\r\neffective learning outcome. <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>5. Students, staff and stakeholders getting together for the\r\npurpose of fullfilling the course objectives.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>6. Emphasis on the individual component  rather than on the overall curriculum to get\r\nbetter learning outcome.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>7. Repeated Training programme about desired and effective\r\nteaching method. e.g:  e-learning, other\r\nnew learning technologies.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>8.Continued motivational activities among the teachers ,\r\nstudents , staffs and other stakeholders to foster appropriate educational\r\nenvirnment for better learning outcome.  <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>9. By increasing the number of trained lecturers.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>9. By increasing the number of number of training among the\r\nlecturers.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed>10. <span xss=removed>By increasing</span>   <span xss=removed>the allocated time for integrated sessions.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed>11. The <span xss=removed>topic which is hard for the students should be found\r\nout by the teachers and</span>  <span xss=removed>extra classes must be taken. <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><o> </o></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><o> </o></p>', '2018-01-18 17:41:38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` (`id`, `assignment_id`, `title`, `msg`, `sent`, `attachment`, `feedback_msg`, `feedback_attachment`, `feedback_at`, `status`) VALUES
(10, 15, 'Assignment: Evaluation of our MBBS curriculum on Anatomy. Identification of its strengths and weaknesses. Suggestions how to improve and implement the curriculum.', '<p>Assignment: Evaluation of our MBBS curriculum on Anatomy.</p><p>Identification of its strengths and weaknessses. Suggestions how to improve and implement the currriculum.</p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Strengths :<o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>1. Well organised.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>2. Structured.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>3. Systematic delivery of content by the teaching stuff.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>4. Specific content.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>4. Specific aims and objectives to acheive the goal.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>5. Outcome base education.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>6. Formative assesment.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>7.Summative assesment.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>7. Comprehensive<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>8. Multiple choice question (MCQ)  in written examination.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>9.  Short answered\r\nquestion (SAQ) instead of long question in written examination.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>10.Inclusion of radiology and imaging oriented anatomy study\r\nand assesment. <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>11.Inclusion of surface anatomy oriented anatomy study and  assesment.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>12. Inclusion of OSPE in practical examination.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>13. Proper sequence of implementation to obtain the aims and\r\nobjectives<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>14. Series of planned activies for specific learning outcome.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>15.Constant monitoing, examination (item,card and term),\r\nevaluation, assesment by the teaching staff.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>16. Small group teaching making the curriculum both student\r\nand teacher centered.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>17. Specifying the curriculum into core content and learning\r\nobjectives. <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>17. well ordered in delivery of component for better learning\r\noutcome.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>18. lecture integrated teaching.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>19. Inclusion of tutorial, practical and demonstration\r\noriented teaching method.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><o> </o></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Weaknesses:<o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>1. In multiple choice question (MCQ) making core curriculum\r\npartially followed.<b><o></o></b></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>2. Questions repeat while preparing multiple choice question and\r\nshort answered question. <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>2. Partially integrated.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>3. Allocated time in order to content is not enough.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>4. Overloaded with examination in order to allocated time.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>5. Relatively less emphasis on clinical oriented anatomy\r\nstudy and assesment.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>6. Clinical part of any Anatomy topic teaching not practical\r\noriented.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>7. Teaching part is not integrated among Anatomy, Physiology\r\nand Biochemistry <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>8. No specific standard, allocation of resources.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>9. No specific standard about educational environment.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>10. Not task oriented.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>11. More teacher centered.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>12. Inclusion of some contents which are usually regarded to\r\nbe of higher level of difficulty e.g . some topic of genetics and nervous\r\nsystem.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><o> </o></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Suggestion  For \r\nImprovement :<o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>1.Task based and problem based teaching should be practiced\r\nmore.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>2. Integrated teaching should be more practiced among\r\nanatomy, physiology and biochemistry.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>3. Resources should be adressed specifically.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>4. Oral examination should be more structured but more flexible\r\nin order to interact with the examinee to facilate her response.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>5.Core content should be more specific in the field of hard\r\ncore, soft core and optional core content.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>6. Time allocation for radiology imaging and surface anatomy\r\nshould be more.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>7. Teaching stuff should be more specific about the\r\nreferences of book<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>8. Evaluation of curriculum by students and teachers may be\r\nfurther analyzed<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>and taken under consideration to upgrade the curriculum.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>9. Curriculum should be more student centered.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>10. Educational environment should be more consensus.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>11. Modification of teaching learning method with more\r\nemphasis on practical examintation.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>12. Some topic and hour from Community medicine should be reduced\r\nand allocated those time to anatomy subject.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>13. Every content should have more specific teaching\r\nmethod  and during  small group \r\nteaching,  application of this\r\nspecific method to all group should be mendatory.  <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed> 14. Simplistic veiw of\r\ncurriculum planning keeping in mind the real challenges of  medical educaton.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>15. Assesment should be developed in parallel with the other\r\naspect of curriculum.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>16.The process of evaluation should be done with the veiws of\r\nstudents, teachers and administrative staff and then should take rapid\r\nintervention and correction of faults.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>17. More emphasis should given on spiral curriculum so that\r\nstudents find more integrated curriculum throughout their course of study.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>  18. Identification of core knowledge that all\r\nstudents need to learn and should occupy two third of the curriculum.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>19. Staff should be appointed with particular expertise in\r\ncurriculum planning, teaching methods and assesment to suport work on the\r\ncurriculum.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>20. Frequent and continous monitoring in the implementations\r\nof all domains of curriculum and that monitoring should be done by undergraduate\r\nmedical education commitee.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>21.Use of study guide and curriculum map by the teaching\r\nstaffs as a method of communication with the students.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed><o> </o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Implementation:<o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>1. Evaluation of curriculum through questionnair to make out\r\nviews of students and   teachers involved\r\nin anatomy teaching.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>2. Integrated teaching should be more implementated.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>3. More emphasis on interprofessional teaching where students\r\nlook at a subject  from the perspective\r\nof other professionals as well as their owns.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>4.Communication between teachers and students to bring\r\neffective learning outcome. <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>5. Students, staff and stakeholders getting together for the\r\npurpose of fullfilling the course objectives.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>6. Emphasis on the individual component  rather than on the overall curriculum to get\r\nbetter learning outcome.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>7. Repeated Training programme about desired and effective\r\nteaching method. e.g:  e-learning, other\r\nnew learning technologies.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>8.Continued motivational activities among the teachers ,\r\nstudents , staffs and other stakeholders to foster appropriate educational\r\nenvirnment for better learning outcome.  <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>9. By increasing the number of trained lecturers.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>9. By increasing the number of number of training among the\r\nlecturers.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed>10. <span xss=removed>By increasing</span>   <span xss=removed>the allocated time for integrated sessions.<o></o></span></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed>11. The <span xss=removed>topic which is hard for the students should be found\r\nout by the teachers and</span>  <span xss=removed>extra classes must be taken. <o></o></span></p>', '2018-01-19 18:10:23', NULL, '<p>Though Majority  of the points are covered but not specifically. strength and weakness should follow the step of planning curriculum. implementation usually demands trained of the faculty,discussion and dialogue with concerned and mapping.</p>', NULL, '2018-01-20 00:10:23', NULL),
