 Shading Accent 6">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="72" SemiHidden="false" UnhideWhenUsed="false" Name="Colorful List Accent 6">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="73" SemiHidden="false" UnhideWhenUsed="false" Name="Colorful Grid Accent 6">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="19" SemiHidden="false" UnhideWhenUsed="false" QFormat="true" Name="Subtle Emphasis">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="21" SemiHidden="false" UnhideWhenUsed="false" QFormat="true" Name="Intense Emphasis">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="31" SemiHidden="false" UnhideWhenUsed="false" QFormat="true" Name="Subtle Reference">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="32" SemiHidden="false" UnhideWhenUsed="false" QFormat="true" Name="Intense Reference">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="33" SemiHidden="false" UnhideWhenUsed="false" QFormat="true" Name="Book Title">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="37" Name="Bibliography">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="39" QFormat="true" Name="TOC Heading">\r\n </w>\r\n&lt;/xml&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n&lt;style&gt;\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n {mso-style-name:"Table Normal";\r\n mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n mso-style-priority:99;\r\n mso-style-parent:"";\r\n mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;\r\n mso-para-margin-top:0in;\r\n mso-para-margin-right:0in;\r\n mso-para-margin-bottom:10.0pt;\r\n mso-para-margin-left:0in;\r\n line-height:115%;\r\n mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n font-size:11.0pt;\r\n font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";\r\n mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;\r\n mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\n mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;\r\n mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\n mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";\r\n mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;}\r\n&lt;/style&gt;\r\n&lt;![endif]--&gt;\r\n\r\n</p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b xss=removed><u><span xss=removed>Strengths</span></u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>1.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>This\r\ncurriculum is based on– </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>a.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Identification of needs</span></b><span xss=removed> according to Wiseman approach, a study of error in practice,\r\ncritical incident studies in community.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>b.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Elaborate aims & objectives</span></b><span xss=removed> are described according to need analysis<span xss=removed>  </span>and according to national goal. For example –\r\nBMDC curriculum to produce doctors who are able to fulfill community needs.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>c.<span xss=removed>      </span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Contents of this curriculum</span></b><span xss=removed> directly contributes to the course objectives, building\r\nblock equip the students with skill or knowledge needed tackle in later part of\r\ncourse & allow students to develop intellectual abilities such as critical\r\nthinking.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>d.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Organization of contents in this curriculum</span></b><span xss=removed> in such a way that there is\r\nrevisiting of topics throughout the course at many levels of difficulty by\r\nintegration.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>e.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Educational strategies </span></b><span xss=removed>are based on both student & teacher centered, problem\r\nbased & information gathering, community oriented & hospital based,\r\nintegrated & systematic.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>f.<span xss=removed>       </span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Teaching methods </span></b><span xss=removed>include both small & large groups, face to face interactive lecture\r\nand individual learning.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>g.<span xss=removed>      </span></span></span><span xss=removed>Both students & course are <b xss=removed>assessed</b> and choice of method depends\r\nupon objectives, local facilities available & experience of local staff.\r\nAssessment is done by MCQ, OSPE, OSCE, written, viva, practical, clinical.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>h.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span><span xss=removed>Details of the curriculum is <b xss=removed>communicated</b> by preparing syllabus,\r\nstudy guide.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>i.<span xss=removed>       </span></span></span><span xss=removed>An ambient, cooperative <b xss=removed>educational<span xss=removed> \r\n</span>environment</b> among student & staff is maintained.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>j.<span xss=removed>       </span></span></span><span xss=removed>All the process be <b xss=removed>managed & maintained</b> by students,\r\nteachers, elected representatives.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>2.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>This\r\ncurriculum provides a lot of development in medical education.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>3.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Time\r\ntable & duration of course of this curriculum is appropriate.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>4.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Details,\r\nelaborate & easy way approach among students, teachers, staff etc were maintained.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b xss=removed><u><span xss=removed>Weaknesses</span></u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>1.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Objectives</span></b><span xss=removed> are too much , descriptive &\r\nmore informative.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>2.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Identification of needs</span></b><span xss=removed> in each discipline senior teachers /\r\npractitioners may have little knowledge or absent in the day of curriculum\r\nplanning.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>3.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Contents of curriculum </span></b><span xss=removed>sometimes too much (i.e.-knowledge of\r\nMRCP in MBBS students) or sometimes less ( Little about USG).</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>4.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Organization of content </span></b><span xss=removed>– 2<sup>nd</sup> & 3<sup>rd</sup>\r\nphase was separated. So without knowledge of pathology & microbiology\r\nstudent has placement in clinical ward. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>5.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Educational strategies</span></b><span xss=removed> is not fully SPICES oriented. No\r\nelectives in this curriculum.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>6.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>In teaching methods </span></b><span xss=removed>sometimes group study may not possible due to lack of proper space. Due\r\nto lack of instruments sometimes individual learning is difficult.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>7.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Proper assessment of students &\r\ncourse </span></b><span xss=removed>may not be\r\npossible due to large number of students, lengthy process of examination, improper\r\ntraining of teacher. Extensive long structures viva in all professional\r\nexaminations still exists.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>8.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Communication of curriculum </span></b><span xss=removed>to the students, teachers, staff, dean & others were\r\npoor. So they have very little knowledge about curriculum.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>9.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Due\r\nto unavoidable sounds from outside sometimes ambient <b xss=removed>educational environment</b> is not possible.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>10.<span xss=removed>  </span></span></span><span xss=removed>All the process may not be <b xss=removed>managed & maintained</b> by students,\r\nteachers, staff as they do not know it.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>11.<span xss=removed>  </span></span></span><span xss=removed>There is no hidden curriculum.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>12.<span xss=removed>  </span></span></span><span xss=removed>Students have little involvement in\r\ncurriculum planning.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b xss=removed><u><span xss=removed>How to improve</span></u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>1.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>All\r\nstaff, teachers, dean & faculty should be trained up.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>2.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Communication\r\nincreases by giving BMDC curriculum to every students, staff, teachers &\r\nrelevant others.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>3.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Every\r\nrelevant person may know about the medical education.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>4.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Basic\r\nprinciple of teaching should be known by teachers.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>5.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>2<sup>nd</sup>\r\n& 3<sup>rd</sup> phase of MBBS course curriculum may be joined together.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>6.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Objective\r\nmay be in short & less descriptive.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>7.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Opinion\r\nof students may involve in curriculum planning.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>8.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Students\r\nmay have more knowledge about Ultrasonogram.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>9.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Problem\r\nbased, integrated, electives, systematic strategy may be applied.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>10.<span xss=removed>  </span></span></span><span xss=removed>Extensive long viva procedure may be\r\nconverted into objective structured practical / clinical examinations\r\n(OSPE/OSCE).</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b xss=removed><u><span xss=removed>How to implement</span></u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>1.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span></b><span xss=removed>The curriculum is not a constant\r\ncomponent must be reviewed time to time. So regular discussion among teachers,\r\nstudents, staff, faculty is mandatory.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>2.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span></b><span xss=removed>Dialogue & criticism about\r\nstrategies among each other is necessary.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>3.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span></b><span xss=removed>Faculty, teachers must be trained up.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p>\r\n\r\n', '2018-01-19 16:30:49', 'upload/attachment/7803c32705b948614bfae1504afb9a89.docx', '<p>Thanks for your works. Most of the points you explain  are satisfactory. your assignment is excellent.</p><p>Prof Md Shah Alam( MBBS, DTCD, MCPS, MMEd)</p><p>Prof & Head, Forensic Medicine, Ibrahim Medical college.</p>', NULL, '2018-01-19 22:30:49', NULL),
(15, 20, 'Discussion on Undergraduate Pediatrics curriculum ', '<p>Fellow: Shaheen Akter</p>', '2018-01-18 16:41:24', 'upload/attachment/fd93501fa459a82835c1280bb98f7c09.docx', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(16, 13, '“Read the curriculum of your discipline- identify the strength and weakness of it, state how to improve and how to implement in your own situation”', '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed>Medical\r\neducation is a life long process and MBBS curriculum is a part of this process.\r\n</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed>Curriculum\r\nis not static, it needs change time to time because there is continuous\r\nchanging in society, disease demography, concepts of learning, assessment\r\nsystem and also due to expansion of medical service and availability of newer\r\ntechnologies.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed>The\r\nundergraduate medical curriculum followed in medical colleges was developed in\r\n1988 through UNDP and WHO supported by the Centre for Medical Education with an\r\naim to produce community oriented doctors who will be able to provide primary\r\nhealth care to the community. From then modification is going on according to\r\nneed and we got Undergraduate Medical Curriculum 2002. After a decade we got\r\nthe updated MBBS Curriculum 2012. I am from Biochemistry discipline.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>The strength of MBBS curriculum\r\nUpdated-2012 of Biochemistry</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>1)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>There\r\nis a National goal to produce competent, compassionate, reflective and\r\ndedicated health care professionals.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>2)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>There\r\nare well stated objectives including Departmental and learning objectives.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>3)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>To\r\nachieve the National goal and course objectives there is a set of learning\r\noutcome.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>4)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>There\r\nare course contents and to achieve the course objectives there is well\r\ndistributed teaching and learning hours.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>5)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>There\r\nare strategy of teaching method by large group teaching, small group teaching\r\nand self learning with the help of mentioned teaching aids.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>6)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>There\r\nare scientific methods of in course evaluation by item examination (oral &\r\nor written) , card final examination (written), practical examination (OSPE and\r\ntraditional practical), Term final examination (written+ oral+Practical\r\n[OSPE+Traditional] ) within available time frame.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>7)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>There\r\nis also Integrated teaching to enrich the curriculum .</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>The weakness of MBBS\r\ncurriculum Updated-2012 of Biochemistry</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>1)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>There\r\nis overlapping of contents with Physiology in two (2) cards named-</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span>a) Renal Biochemistry,\r\nbody fluid, electrolytes and acid base balance</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span>b) Clinical\r\nBiochemistry and Endocrinology</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed>2) Difficulties in completion of course content in scheduled\r\ntime</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed>3) There is no clear instructions about self learning that is\r\nassignment and self assessment.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>      </span>4) In evaluation procedure,</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span>a) There is no proper\r\nguideline about Multiple choice questions (MCQ)</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>     </span><span xss=removed> </span><span xss=removed> </span>b) There is no proper guideline about OSPE</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>      </span><span xss=removed> </span>c)\r\nThere is no standard and uniformed checklist for procedure station</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>     </span>5) Lack of skilled staffs in medical\r\ncolleges to implement this curriculum <span xss=removed> </span>properly</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Steps for improvement :</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>1)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>The\r\ncontents in two (2) cards named-</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span>a) Renal Biochemistry,\r\nbody fluid, electrolytes and acid base balance</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span>b) Clinical\r\nBiochemistry and Endocrinology </span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed>should be clearly demarcated, that is it should be very clear\r\nthat what topics the students should go through in Physiology and what in\r\nBiochemistry. </span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed>I think, then it will be more student centered and students\r\nwill not be overburdened and time will be properly managed to complete the\r\ncourse content.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>2)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>There\r\nshould be a proper guideline about MCQ so that it can improve the knowledge,\r\nskills and attitude of students.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>3)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>There\r\nshould be a proper guideline about OSPE considering different domains of\r\nobjectives and OSPE should be conducted centrally.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>4)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>There\r\nshould be standard and uniformed checklist for procedure station and that\r\nshould be practiced in all medical colleges.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>5)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>There\r\nshould be clear instructions about self learning that is assignment and self\r\nassessment.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>6)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Formative\r\nassessment procedure should be maintained by all medical colleges.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>7)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span>Small group teaching and Problem based\r\nlearning should be practiced by adequate number of skilled teaching staffs.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>8)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>There\r\nis integrated teaching in our curriculum but it should be practiced by all\r\nmedical colleges.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>9)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span>Adequate number of skilled teaching and\r\ntechnical staffs should be ensured in all medical colleges by the specific body\r\nof Government.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>10)<span xss=removed>                       \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Promotion\r\nof an appropriate educational environment which is the soul and spirit of\r\nmedical curriculum. Collaborative rather than competitive environment helps\r\nstudents to learn and to develop a spirit of team work.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>11)<span xss=removed>                       \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Resources\r\nneeded to deliver the curriculum which may be lecture hall, laboratory space\r\nand laboratory equipments, sufficient number of tutorial rooms should be\r\nensured in all medical colleges by the specific body of Government.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Implementation :</span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>1)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Experts\r\nof Biochemistry and Physiology will focus on the overlapping contents of above\r\nmentioned cards and make it well defined and student centered.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>2)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>MCQs\r\nand OSPEs can be collected from different medical colleges and a question bank\r\ncan be made. Wokshops on preparation of MCQ and preparation and conduction of OSPE\r\ncan be conducted in different medical colleges under the supervision of experts\r\nof CME.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>3)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>To\r\naugment the core curriculum some elective program related to core like project\r\nwork can be added, which will facilitate higher level of objectives.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>4)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span>Elective programme like computer literacy\r\nprogramme can be added which will help student in E-learning.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>5)<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span>All medical colleges should maintain Medical\r\neducation units to develop skilled teaching staffs for proper implementation of\r\ncurriculum to achieve the National goal and It should be monitored by\r\nGovernment regularly.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed>Curriculum is a continuous, never ending process. So the\r\nneeds of the individual students, educational institutions and the community\r\nmust be assessed and this dynamic process works best in an environment\r\nconductive to learning, thrives on monitoring, quality assurance and continuous\r\nquality improvement. </span></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><i></i><u></u><sub></sub><sup></sup><strike></strike><br></p>', '2018-01-18 16:52:54', 'upload/attachment/70ff3714c2633ec0564a03f4ffed02f3.doc', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
