="Colorful Shading Accent 6">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="72" SemiHidden="false" UnhideWhenUsed="false" Name="Colorful List Accent 6">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="73" SemiHidden="false" UnhideWhenUsed="false" Name="Colorful Grid Accent 6">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="19" SemiHidden="false" UnhideWhenUsed="false" QFormat="true" Name="Subtle Emphasis">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="21" SemiHidden="false" UnhideWhenUsed="false" QFormat="true" Name="Intense Emphasis">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="31" SemiHidden="false" UnhideWhenUsed="false" QFormat="true" Name="Subtle Reference">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="32" SemiHidden="false" UnhideWhenUsed="false" QFormat="true" Name="Intense Reference">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="33" SemiHidden="false" UnhideWhenUsed="false" QFormat="true" Name="Book Title">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="37" Name="Bibliography">\r\n  <w Locked="false" Priority="39" QFormat="true" Name="TOC Heading">\r\n </w>\r\n&lt;/xml&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n&lt;style&gt;\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n {mso-style-name:"Table Normal";\r\n mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n mso-style-priority:99;\r\n mso-style-parent:"";\r\n mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;\r\n mso-para-margin:0in;\r\n mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n font-size:10.0pt;\r\n font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";}\r\n&lt;/style&gt;\r\n&lt;![endif]--&gt;\r\n\r\n</p><p class="MsoNormal"><span xss=removed>Objectives:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol xss=removed start="1" type="1"><li class="MsoNormal" xss=removed>Evaluation of current curriculum</li><li class="MsoNormal" xss=removed>Ways of improvement and implementation</li></ol>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span xss=removed>Introduction:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Curriculum refers to a series of planned activities intended\r\nto bring about specific learning outcomes in the student. There are ten basic\r\nquestions are considered before planning a curriculum and there remain five\r\naspects of a curriculum. Depending up on these basic facts in curriculum the\r\nexisting MBBS curriculum is evaluated and an attempt is made to improve it.<span xss=removed></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span xss=removed>Given/current\r\ncurriculum:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">In the 2012 curriculum, in urinary system there remain five\r\ntopics namely glomerulonephritis, nephrotic syndrome, acute kidney injury,\r\nchronic kidney disease and urinary tract infection. And the set learning objectives\r\nare there. Integrated teaching included rheumatic fever and nephrotic syndrome.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span xss=removed>Overall\r\nstrength:</span> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Bangladesh Medical and Dental Council have a curriculum with\r\nits defined learning objectives. May it not be flaw free, but its presence and\r\npractice is important.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Now the evaluation Nephrology part in detail is presented. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span xss=removed>Need\r\nassessment:</span> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">The current curriculum is sufficiently justified in\r\nfulfilling the community needs. It encompassed the common renal diseases\r\nidentifiable in community that may be treated in primary care and some patients\r\nwill require secondary and tertiary care level services. Still there should be\r\na room for further improvements in need assessment especially by critical\r\nincident studies for example star fruit can cause acute kidney injury. So, it\r\nmight be included in future that common edible agents with nephrotoxic\r\npotentials.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span xss=removed>Aims and\r\nobjectives:</span> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">In the existing curriculum, the objectives are clearly\r\nmentioned. So, there is very little, if any, to improve in this area, rather to\r\nme, there remain some areas of specialists’ concern like arterio-venous\r\nfistula, renal allografts etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span xss=removed>Contents:</span>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">The contents of existing curriculum included AKI, CKD,\r\nglomerulonephritis, nephrotic syndrome and urinary tract infection. These broad\r\nareas of renal diseases are quiet sufficient to address the community needs.\r\nEmerging diseases are to be emphasis in future. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span xss=removed>Organization\r\nof contents:</span> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Because of the vertical organization of current curriculum,\r\nclinically relevant basic subjects are incorporated in first two academic\r\nyears, and then in fourth year students are to learn Para clinical subjects. If\r\na horizontal integration could be made especially in to topics like\r\npost-streptococcal glomerulonephritis and urinary tract infections to involve\r\nmedicine, nephrology, pediatrics, pathology, microbiology, pharmacology,\r\ncommunity medicine in integrated teaching, definitely it could achieve a better\r\nlearning outcome.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span xss=removed>Educational\r\nstrategies:</span> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">This appears to be of discipline based. If direction is\r\ngiven towards problem based and integrated, then it would be better.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span xss=removed>Teaching\r\nmethods to be used: </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">In the present curriculum 5 hours are allocated to cover\r\nmajor parts of nephrology related topics. It will be more helpful to the\r\nstudent if it is problem solving and improvement in communication skills.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span xss=removed>Assessment:</span>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Very little is extracted from the current curriculum\r\nregarding assessment in nephrology except one Item in card 1. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span xss=removed>Communication\r\nof the curriculum:</span> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">There is an existing curriculum but is not communicated at\r\nall (if any) to clinical teachers and students of respective course. It is\r\nprobably because of ignorance of the presence of curriculum by many clinical\r\nteachers. Many clinical staffs do not know how much is to teach to a 3<sup>rd</sup>\r\nyear clinical placement or a 5<sup>th</sup> year clinical placement. Students\r\ndo not know the existence of the curriculum. So, this communication should be\r\nemphasized for both teachers and student to attain a better learning outcome.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span xss=removed>Educational\r\nenvironment:</span> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">In resource-constrain setting like ours the appropriate\r\nattainment of an appropriate educational environment is often impossible. During\r\na bedside teaching, it is almost impossible to create a calm environment. It is\r\nquiet impossible to give proper attention to 24 students, or supervise or teach\r\nexamination technique to all student in a single 2 hour class. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span xss=removed>Management\r\nof the overall process:</span> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">In the light of five basic aspects of curriculum namely\r\naims, content, organization of contents, learning methods and assessment, the\r\n2012 undergraduate medical curriculum encompassing nephrology addresses almost\r\nall areas. But, there are weaknesses in descriptions of learning methods to be\r\nused for given tasks and ways of assessment. A better description in these\r\nareas is likely to bring about an expected learning outcome.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span xss=removed>Conclusion:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Overall weakness of the curriculum is the inadequacy in\r\ngiven time for development of communication skills, lack of evaluation and feedback\r\nby the students regarding the course and teachers. For implementation of the\r\nproposed activities, a subject committee may be formed to identify areas for\r\nfurther improvement. These proposals might be communicated with the medicine\r\ndepartment and phase 3 meetings. Ultimately at national level during curriculum\r\ndevelopment these issues should be raised and incorporated in undergraduate\r\nmedical curriculum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"> </p>\r\n\r\n', '2018-01-19 07:16:28', 'upload/attachment/fdad3205523624b7683b3e9a9dc36ac0.doc', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(20, 12, 'Identification of the strengths and weaknesses of this curriculum & its improvement and implementation strategies.', '<p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>I am an Assistant Professor of\r\nthe department of Biochemistry in a private medical college. We follow the “Curriculum\r\nfor Under-graduate Medical Education in Bangladesh – Updated 2012” which has\r\nbeen implemented from session 2012-2013. This curriculum has made as\r\nneed-based, community oriented & competency based. Now, I want to discuss about\r\nthe strength and weakness of this curriculum & its improvement and implementation\r\nstrategies.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Strengths\r\nof the curriculum:<o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>In\r\nSyllabus:<o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>1.<span xss=removed>    </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Learning\r\nobjectives & course contents are clearly defined for both teachers &\r\nstudents.</span><span xss=removed><o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>2.<span xss=removed>    </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Students\r\ncan apply the impact of Biochemistry in medicine from early years of course.\r\nFor example, they attain the skill to perform common bedside biochemical tests\r\n& to interpret common biochemical tests in diagnosis of diseases.</span><span xss=removed><o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>3.<span xss=removed>    </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Syllabus\r\nhas structured & shortened by omitting topics overlapped with other\r\ndiscipline.</span><span xss=removed><o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>4.<span xss=removed>    </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Students\r\ncan complete the course properly within limited time frame as teaching hours\r\nare clearly defined.</span><span xss=removed><o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>5.<span xss=removed>    </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Addition\r\nof integrated teaching helps students to co-ordinate among different subjects.</span><span xss=removed><o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>In course\r\nevaluation:<o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>1.<span xss=removed>    </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Evaluation\r\nof students has become more structured & less time consuming.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>2.<span xss=removed>    </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Students\r\ncan be easily assessed due to addition of appropriate methods (SAQ and SOE) in\r\ncurriculum.</span><span xss=removed><o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Weaknesses\r\nof the Curriculum</span></b><span xss=removed>:<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Ø<span xss=removed>  </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>The\r\ncontents are not clearly described in all cards. For example, in core content\r\nof clinical biochemistry, lipid profile and dyslipoproteinemias are added. But\r\nthe learning objective is to teach; lipid profile and their clinical\r\nimportance. So it becomes confusing.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Ø<span xss=removed>  </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Teachers\r\nare not well trained for this curriculum both in teaching and evaluating\r\nstudents. Many teachers do not go through learning objectives; they teach more\r\nthan the objectives; also do questions beyond objective. <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Ø<span xss=removed>  </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Most\r\nof the teachers do not know how to make SAQ questions. They often use the term\r\n‘Describe’ or ‘Discuss’ which is not feasible with the questions of 3 or 4\r\nmarks. So, students become confused in answering questions.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Ø<span xss=removed>  </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>There\r\nis no written instruction for evaluation of answer sheet. Marks differ widely\r\namong the examiners of same question. So, all students are not equally\r\nassessed.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Ø<span xss=removed>  </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Many\r\nconventional teachers do not go through SOE, they like to ask questions\r\nwhatever they like.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Ø<span xss=removed>  </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>SOE\r\nand OSPE questions vary from college to college, and sometimes questions are\r\nnot standard enough.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Ø<span xss=removed>  </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Integrated\r\nteaching method cannot be applied properly due to lack of training.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Improvement strategies</span></b><b><span xss=removed>:</span></b><b><span xss=removed><o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Ø<span xss=removed> </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>The\r\ncourse contents should be revised and should be more specific and clear.</span><span xss=removed><o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Ø<span xss=removed> </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Learning\r\nmethods should be determined by the desired outcome.</span><span xss=removed><o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Ø<span xss=removed> </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Answer\r\nkey for SAQ assessment should be given to examiners for equal evaluation of all\r\nstudents.</span><span xss=removed><o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Ø<span xss=removed> </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Central\r\nmonitoring is needed.</span><span xss=removed><o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Ø<span xss=removed> </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Trained\r\n& committed teaching staff is needed for curriculum improvement.</span><span xss=removed><o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Implementation\r\nstrategies:<o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Ø<span xss=removed>  </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Teachers need time & opportunities (e.g. yearly\r\ntraining) to become familiar with new curriculum. <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Ø<span xss=removed>  </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>By raising awareness among teachers about new curriculum.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Ø<span xss=removed>  </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>By piloting the new curriculum.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Ø<span xss=removed>  </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>By faculty development for adequate training with a\r\nsample three day training program.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Ø<span xss=removed>  </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>By planning strategies to promote & use the\r\ncurriculum.<o></o></span></p>', '2018-01-19 15:47:27', NULL, '<p>Thanks for your excellent job to go through  your biochemistry curriculum. But you should remember that your unit was curriculum planning & development. The objectives of preparing assignment  is to assess your knowledge & skill regarding conception of curriculum planning. Please rewrite the <b>strength</b> and <b>weakness</b> according to the hardens''s  ten questions  in planning of a curriculum. if any further queiry</p><p>wish your good luck.</p><p>Prof Md shah Alam (MBBS,DTCD,MCPS,MMEd)</p><p>Prof & Head, Forensic Medicine, Ibrahim Medical College</p><p>Mob-01711237708</p>', NULL, '2018-01-19 21:47:27', NULL),
