 Clinical part of any Anatomy topic teaching not practical\r\noriented.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>7. Teaching part is not integrated among Anatomy, Physiology\r\nand Biochemistry <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>8. No specific standard, allocation of resources.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>9. No specific standard about educational environment.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>10. Not task oriented.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>11. More teacher centered.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>12. Inclusion of some contents which are usually regarded to\r\nbe of higher level of difficulty e.g . some topic of genetics and nervous\r\nsystem.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><o> </o></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Suggestion  For \r\nImprovement :<o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>1.Task based and problem based teaching should be practiced\r\nmore.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>2. Integrated teaching should be more practiced among\r\nanatomy, physiology and biochemistry.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>3. Resources should be adressed specifically.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>4. Oral examination should be more structured and  more flexible in order to interact with the\r\nexaminee to facilate her response.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>5. Core content should be more specific in the field of hard\r\ncore, soft core and optional core content.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>6. Time allocation for radiology imaging and surface anatomy\r\nshould be more.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>7. Teaching stuff should be more specific about the\r\nreferences of book<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>8. Evaluation of curriculum by students and teachers may be\r\nfurther analyzed<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>and taken under consideration to upgrade the curriculum.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>9. Curriculum should be more student centered.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>10.  Educational\r\nenvironment should be more consensus.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>11. Modification of teaching learning method with more\r\nemphasis on practical examintation.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>12. Some topic and hour from Community medicine should be reduced\r\nand allocated those time to anatomy subject.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>13. Every content should have more specific teaching\r\nmethod  and during  small group \r\nteaching,  application of this\r\nspecific method to all small group should be mendatory.  <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed> 14. Simplistic veiw of\r\ncurriculum planning keeping in mind the real challenges of  medical educaton.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>15. Assesment  should\r\nbe developed in parallel with the other aspect of curriculum.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>16.The process of evaluation should be done with the veiws of\r\nstudents, teachers and administrative staff and then should take rapid\r\nintervention and correction of faults.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>17. More emphasis should given on spiral curriculum so that\r\nstudents find more integrated curriculum throughout their course of study.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>  18. More specific  core knowledge that all students need to learn\r\nand should occupy two third of the curriculum.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>19. Staff should be appointed with particular expertise in\r\ncurriculum planning, teaching methods and assesment to suport work on the\r\ncurriculum.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>20. Frequent and continous monitoring in the implementation\r\nof all domains of curriculum and the monitoring should be done by undergraduate\r\nmedical education commitee.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>21.Use of study guide and curriculum map by the teaching\r\nstaffs as a method of communication with the students  through out the course tract.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed><o> </o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Implementation:<o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>1. Evaluation of curriculum through questionnair to make out\r\nviews of students and   teachers involved\r\nin anatomy teaching.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>2. Integrated teaching should be more implemented.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>3. More emphasis on interprofessional teaching where students\r\nlook at a subject  from the perspective\r\nof other professionals as well as their owns.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>4.Communication between teachers and students to bring effective\r\nlearning outcome. <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>5. Students, staff and stakeholders getting together for the\r\npurpose of fullfilling the course objectives.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>6. More emphasis on the individual component  rather than on the overall curriculum to get\r\nbetter learning outcome.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>7. Repeated Training programme about desired and effective\r\nteaching method. e.g:  e-learning, other\r\nnew learning technologies.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>8.Continued motivational activities among the teachers ,\r\nstudents , staffs and other stakeholders to facilitate  appropriate educational environment for better\r\nlearning outcome.  <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>9. By increasing the number of trained careers lecturer.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>9. By increasing the number of number of training among the\r\nlecturers.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed>10. <span xss=removed>By increasing</span>   <span xss=removed>the allocated time for integrated sessions.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed>11. The <span xss=removed>topic which is hard for the students should be found\r\nout by the teachers and</span>  <span xss=removed>extra classes must be taken. <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><o> </o></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><o> </o></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><o> </o></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o> </o></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o> </o></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class="MsoNormal"><o> </o></p>', '2018-01-19 13:56:18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(33, 25, 'Strengths and Limitations of Surgical Discipline of “Curriculum for Under-graduate Medical Education in Bangladesh- Updated 2012”', '<p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Introduction:<o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>Our\r\nnew curriculum of medical education heading as “Curriculum for Under-graduate\r\nMedical Education in Bangladesh- Updated 2012” is a very well written and\r\nideally developed curriculum ever since. It is developed keeping in mind all\r\nthe ten questions needed to be addressed during curriculum planning. <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Strengths: <o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>Aims\r\nand objectives of the curriculum covered all aspects of surgical discipline.\r\nContents are detailed and have included all the allied disciplines namely\r\nOrthopedics, Radiology, Radiotherapy, Transfusion Medicine, Anesthesiology,\r\nNeuro-surgery, Pediatric-surgery, Burn, plastic and reconstructive surgery,\r\nEmergency & Casualty, Dentistry, Ophthalmology, Otolaryngology. The\r\ncontents are well documented and well organized. The starting is as traditional\r\nmedical curriculum while basic sciences are taught for one and a half year in\r\nphase I, whereas, spirally integrated in subsequent phases (II, III, and IV) so\r\nthat competence of the students increases with each visit to a topic. The\r\nstrategy adopted in this curriculum is a mixture of approaches both innovative\r\n(SPICES) and traditional. Teaching methods are logically arranged including\r\nlectures, tutorials, practical, demonstrations, clinical and bed-side teaching.\r\nIt also included integrated teaching for twenty hours in each course.\r\nManipulative and practical skills are precisely listed which covers most of the\r\nrequirements in surgical patient management. Small group teaching included\r\ntutorials, problem-based learning, clinical demonstrations (OPD/Indoor), attending\r\nand observing minor operations, demonstrations of X-rays and specimens,\r\nobservation in ICU and post-operative ward, case presentation and discussions.\r\nThere are provision of assignments and scope of self-study. Traditional and\r\nmodern teaching aids are suggested to use namely chalk & board, OHP,\r\nspecimens, plain & contrast X-rays of various systems, ultrasonograph,\r\nisotope scan, CT scan, MRI, computer, multimedia, photographs and videos,\r\nmodels etc. Assessment portion is also well organized namely item examination,\r\ncard final and term examination, final examination (written, oral, practical,\r\nclinical). The whole syllabus is organized with a precise time-table in each\r\nacademic calendar. This curriculum also included the topic those were not\r\naddressed in the previous one like communication skills, professional attitude\r\nand understanding of ethical principles, preventive and palliative care etc. <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Limitations:  <o></o></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>The\r\nsurgical needs in our community is not outlined, instead, a vague term “common\r\nsurgical problems” was used which remains on the discretions of the faculties,\r\nhence, very much subjective one. I think the term “common” must be precisely\r\ndefined and specified, otherwise, a common problem to one may seem to be rare\r\nto another faculty. For example, Cystic Hygroma though rare in our country get\r\nmuch importance in teaching and examination while infective problems other than\r\nabscess including surgical site infections get least importance. A study of\r\nerrors and critical incidence studies are neglected in the contents. To give\r\nimportance to a wide range of allied subjects, the contents are overcrowded\r\ncreating burden to the students and compel to surface learning. Much time is\r\nallocated for lectures (five hundred and twenty hours) while only sixty-two hours\r\nfor clinical/bed-side teaching. This makes theoretical giant and practical\r\ndwarf doctors.  Educational environment\r\nis detailed but practically this environment is very difficult to achieve and\r\nmaintain without supervision so there are great variations of educational\r\nenvironment among medical colleges. Moreover, there is no guideline regarding\r\ntutorial rooms, wards, and patient-student ratio. That is why students of a\r\nlarge number of medical colleges have poor clinical and practical exposure. The\r\ncurriculum management portion is also much neglected. There is no guideline to\r\nstaff requirements, teacher-student ratio and staff development program. So,\r\nthough the curriculum is new teachers remained traditional and inadequate.\r\nLogistical support requirements are not defined and there are great variations\r\namong institutions. Thus, questions adopted in examinations lack variations,\r\npractically most of the questions are set from questions bank. Evaluation\r\nsystem is theoretically upgraded but difficult to implement in most\r\ninstitutions because of inadequate teaching and support staffs. Marks in\r\nformative assessment is very small and subjective. This discourages students’\r\nday to day learning. There is nothing about academic standards and quality\r\nassurance in this curriculum. So, there are gaps among the declared curriculum,\r\ntaught curriculum and learned curriculum. <o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Conclusions:<o></o></span></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>Despite\r\nhaving much strength in many aspects of the new curriculum, difficulty in\r\nimplementation, lack of standards among institutions, inadequate arrangement\r\nfor continuous staff development, disharmonious assessment, and insufficient\r\nacademic standards and quality assurance have converted this curriculum\r\npractically to a little better than a syllabus. Curriculum needs regular\r\nperiodic review and necessary modification and changes time to time. So, we\r\ndon’t expect to get the curriculum fully appropriate at one point of review and\r\nassume required changes will be done while learning from errors, changes in\r\nmedicine and our community needs.    <o></o></span></p>', '2018-01-20 01:09:22', 'upload/attachment/71d049bc849a37bbaf953f9921b4417f.docx', '<p>Well written</p><p>However, suggestions for improvement and ways of implementation could have been specified more<br></p>', NULL, '2018-01-20 07:09:22', NULL),
(34, 16, 'Assignment on curriculum development', '<p>Sir,</p><p>Assalamu Alaikum. Please see the attachment for assignment. </p><p>With Due Respect,</p><p>Dr. Masum</p>', '2018-01-21 04:43:31', 'upload/attachment/877b7cb11ca6a565423ab887b7b3cdff.docx', '<p>Dear fellow.</p><p>Probably you failed to understand the feed back.  your first assignment was better than later. You are advised to resubmit assignment as per feedback, at or before 8 am on next day( 22.1.18).</p><p>prof Md Shah Alam</p><p>Your assignment need resubmit according to feedback.<br></p>', NULL, '2018-01-21 10:43:31', NULL),
(35, 12, 'Identification of the strengths and weaknesses of this curriculum & its improvement and implementation strategies.', '<p><span xss=removed>Identification of the strengths and weaknesses of this curriculum & its improvement and implementation strategies.</span><br></p>', '2018-01-21 04:26:19', 'upload/attachment/8aba1edfc6446a2ebebfd050b463a9c0.docx', '<p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>Thanks for your effort.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed>The <b>strength </b>and <b>improvement aspect</b>  of your assignment\r\nsatisfy  80% of the underpinning concept\r\nof expected points; But the  <b>weakness </b>does not meet the expected points.\r\nThe mentioned points  don’t  address curriculum  weakness rather   lacking of \r\nimplementation strategies. The <b>implementation\r\n strategies </b>usually done by\r\ndiscussion, training, dialogue etc;  underpin concept of implement strategies of your assignment  can be accepted.<o></o></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" xss=removed><span xss=removed><o> </o></span></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<span xss=removed>Prof Md Shah Alam</span></p><p><span xss=removed>Dated : 21.1.18.<br></span><br></p>', NULL, '2018-01-21 10:26:19', NULL),
(36, 16, 'strengths , weaknesses , improvement and implementation of curriculum.', '<p>Sir,</p><p>Please see the attachment.</p>', '2018-01-22 02:09:45', 'upload/attachment/cbc58e330886ffd9fa278109507ee969.docx', '<p>Dear fellow.</p><p>Your assignment is accepted. But it would be better if you describe your assignments under the principal aspect of curriculum planning. You know the curriculum and syllabus is not same. Curriculum is a detail roadmap for educational program. Major part of a curriculum is vision,mission, goals, aim & objectives,Content, Teaching learning methods/ strategies,Learning experience,Assessment & evaluation.</p><p>Wish your best luck </p><p>Prof  Md Shah Alam</p>', NULL, '2018-01-22 08:09:45', NULL),
