(79, 49, 'Describe the importance of taxonomy & learning objective in educational program. Write at least 5 specific objectives on any topic of my specialty according to the hierarchies in each learning domain.', 'Dr. Md. Towhidur Rahman    I/D – GD2GOB\r\nAssignment no -2 (M1U2)\r\nName of assignment – Describe the importance of taxonomy & learning objective in educational program. Write at least 5 specific objectives on any topic of my specialty according to the hierarchies in each learning domain.\r\n\r\nImportance of taxonomy in educational program:\r\nTaxonomies \r\nTaxonomies of learning are the hierarchical classification in the field of education, have been developed by various groups concern with educational problems to help teachers to formulate precisely the educational objective. Taxonomy guides in grouping of objectives into types of learning capabilities utilized to plan the conditions required for successful learning, to determine the sequence of a segment of course to formulate instructional design and evaluation system.\r\n1. Taxonomy usually help to classify learning objectives; setting learning experience & learning objectives are the basis for designing curriculum, content evaluation.\r\n2. Indicates the type of learning outcomes that should be considered.\r\n3. Provides a framework for classifying those outcomes.\r\n4. It is the backbone of many teaching philosophies, in particular, those that lean more towards skills rather than content.\r\n5. Forms the blueprint for forming the assessment tools.\r\n6. Provides common grounds & makes comparison of various teaching programs easier.\r\n7. Directs attention towards changes in student performance in a variety of areas.\r\n   Importance of learning objective in educational program:\r\nEducational objectives describe in term possible exactly what a student should think, act or feel at the end of a learning experience. Education is the process involving to facilitate learning, the chief goal of which is to bring about change in the behavior. The sort of behavioral changes that the school attempts to bring about constitute the educational objectives.\r\n\r\n1. Learning objectives are the basis for designing curriculum, content, evaluation.\r\n2. It guides planning instruction / lesson – By developing learning objectives for a course we can more rationally sequence instruction, allot time to topics, assemble materials, prepare outlines and booklists etc.\r\n3. It serves as a guidelines for providing instruction.\r\n4. It guides for assessment & evaluation.\r\n5. It guides for curriculum planning.\r\n6. Facilitating evaluation -  Learning objectives can facilitate various evaluation activities, evaluating students, evaluating instruction.\r\n7. Aiding in communication with others – There is need to communicate learning objectives to others: between instructor & student, with other instructors.\r\n8. Improving instruction -  If we intend to improve instruction in a particular lesson or course, we usually begin with the learning objectives for that lesson or course.\r\n9. Producing new insights – The process of clarifying objectives may produce major changes in those who engage in the effort.\r\n10. It guides the selection of content.\r\n11. It helps in development of an instructional strategy.\r\n12. For development & selection of instructional materials.\r\n13. For construction of tests & other instruments for assessing & then evaluating student learning outcomes.\r\n\r\n\r\nSpecific objectives on Ultrasound (USG) guided aspiration of pleural effusion (topic-Radiology & Imaging) according to the hierarchies in each learning domain:\r\n      Cognitive domain – \r\n1. To describe the pleural effusion for USG guided aspiration in sitting position of patient (Remembering).\r\n2. To explain the mechanism of pleural effusion in dependant part of chest (Understanding).\r\n3. To demonstrate the amount of pleural effusion in USG & for aspirate (Applying).\r\n4. To compare the right side / left side pleural effusion in USG for aspirate (Analyzing).\r\n5. To evaluate the pleural effusion in USG against consolidation / collapse for aspirate (Evaluating).\r\n6. To summarize the absence of haematoma, Amount of fluid taken within 10% of the amount required, not more than two attempts, not very painful to patients during aspiration of USG guided pleural fluid (Creating).\r\nPsychomotor domain –\r\n1. To diagnose the pleural effusion in sitting position of patient on examination bed for USG guided aspiration (Perception).\r\n2. To prepare by blood set needle, sitting beside the patient for USG guided pleural fluid aspiration (Set).\r\n3. To perform USG guided introduce the needle under the guidance of instructor for pleural fluid aspiration (Guided response).\r\n4. To construct the aspiration of USG guided pleural fluid with confidence & proficiency (Mechanism).\r\n5. To build up efficiency of USG guided pleural fluid aspiration (Complex overt response).\r\n6. To alter the site of aspiration if there is any difficulty in collection of USG guided pleural fluid (Adaptations).\r\n7. To show a new method of USG guided pleural fluid aspiration in decubitus position (Organization).\r\n\r\nAffective domain –\r\n1. To assure of the pain of the patient during procedure of USG guided pleural fluid aspiration (Receiving).\r\n2. To take safety measure of the patient about little painful procedure of USG guided pleural fluid aspiration (Responding).\r\n3. To satisfy the patient about the findings of pleural fluid & a sufficient commitment to promote it (Valuing).\r\n4. To encourage the patient & his family that ready to help them to get over it (Organization).\r\n5. To believe that integration of the value into a total philosophy in such a way that it becomes a predictable behavioral characteristic (Characterization by a value complex).\r\n', '2018-01-28 13:05:13', 'upload/attachment/a9743de4402c5c6d85a3f952857e04ff.docx', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
