(124, 80, 'Assignment-1 “Online Environment is merely an Extension of Face-to-Face Learning Environment”-Discuss why Assignment-2 Describe the Process of E-learning (EL) and its Role in Continuing Professional Development (CPD)', 'Assignment-1\r\n“Online Environment is merely an Extension of Face-to-Face Learning Environment”-Discuss why\r\nTraditional learning is time-tested and valued for long. It has many pros and cons. Online (OL) learning is a new system of teaching learning first introduced in 2002 and rapidly gaining acceptance. It has many advantages over traditional learning, but not also without limitations. Blending system including both traditional and online are complementary and provide maximum benefits to the learners. When considered together online learning environment provide support as an extension of service that is provided by face-to-face (FtF) learning environment. There are many causes as mentioned below:\r\n1. Traditional learning environment provide age oriented learning opportunity from primary school through to university level. There are little or no scope of on-campus learning facility for elderly people who feel to keep learning out of boredom or curiosity. OL learning environment provides various courses for them.\r\n2. Not all students can avail facility of traditional learning because of medical condition or disability. They can avail OL courses for study. \r\n3. Some learners need school transfer due to change of locations of parents’ job. They can avail OL learning to continue with the same school from their new location. \r\n4. Those who are doing job, continue learning OL with same academic calendar as their institutions that provide courses. They can take classes at their time they wish. \r\n5. Traditional learning provides much life experiences and OL also provides experience from discussion forum, synchronous communication and instant chat.\r\n6. FtF learning provides more value to college degree, allow to meet service providers who hires alumni from college, whereas, OL provide with special service oriented skills which also help to get job. FtF allows access to equipment and facilities to improve knowledge about a subject in a campus. OL focus on improving skill and make marketable leading to polished and development of job related skills. \r\n7. FtF give general critical thinking skill but may not get hands on experience of what you learn. Thus get tough to do a task in professional life, whereas, OL helps in such situation with relevant skills about subject. \r\n8. FtF is expensive, OL cuts off expenditure to a half and thus allows learners to continue study. \r\n9. Those engaged in FtF and travel extensively need not interruption of study if OL facilities are available in his institutes.\r\n10. In FtF tutors are available to interact to teach to assess and to provide feedback and in OL learners can contact tutors when needed instantly, also has the opportunity of self-assessment.\r\n11. FtF learning is directed by teachers/supervisors/guides and learners become self-dependent, self-regulated and self-directed in OL environment. \r\nThus where FtF stops/limits its service OL environment continue with the learners to solve the limitations. \r\nAssignment-2\r\nDescribe the Process of E-learning (EL) and its Role in Continuing Professional Development (CPD)\r\nThere are some common phases that any EL development process must undergo. There are a fair number of instructional design modules. Whatever module is chosen, the module itself is followed quite rigidly. In EL each organization follows its own process that fits into its way of functioning. There are some common faces that are followed. These are:\r\n1. Creation of instructional design (IDD)- This is a high level plan of overall instructional approaches of the course. Some approaches are problem-solving, avatars and scenarios. It is also decided how the content need to be broken down to courses, modules and scenarios. Each course is to be created using a different IDD strategy, dealt with in the IDD. Instructional and visual elements are finalized.\r\n2. Scripting- Contents of each course is broadly finalized and divided into modules and the content for each screen within each module is decided on. Interactivities, assessment, activities and resources for each module are finalized. Narrative script is finalized. Form of script may be word document of power-point presentations.\r\n3. Development of a prototype- This is a complete representation of entire course in a few slides. On screen content and audio scripts are created and finalized. Important elements are picked up for the course and a functional prototype is created. Final decision is made about how contents will be presented on screen, interactivities, activities/assignments added, colors, images, animations and additional resources provided. The prototype needs to be functional on the learning management system.\r\n4. Development of the course without audio- Fully functional course is made ready and approved without audio. May need changes in content, narration, and animation etc. before approval. \r\n5. Development of the course audio- Audio script is finalized, synchronized with animations and on screen text and fully functioning course with audio is ready. \r\n6. Creation of learning management system version- This is the final step is mostly mechanical and technical one. Once get the final approval the course is ready to be hosted on the learning platform and go “live”. Technical take care at this stage. \r\nEach face of the process of EL development need approval before going to the next step. Thus at the end of the day a successful course is created and learners get a course that helps them learn. \r\nRole of EL in CPD\r\nEL has the potential in the delivery of CPD services online. Professionals are time constrained and price sensitive, naturally strong independent learners making them good candidates for EL services. \r\n1. EL provides customized or personalized curriculum that is needed by individual students. \r\n2. Learning is made available at a time and place that is optimal for the learner.\r\n3. Provide access to teachers and resources from any place at any time world-wide.\r\n4. Learners work together more closely and more meaningfully.\r\n5. Access to interactive content.\r\n6. Access to simulations, ability to rehearse scenarios and procedures thus accelerate expertise.\r\nThe followings are the primary service components for OL CPD:\r\n1. Personal development planner\r\n2. CPD port folio tracker\r\n3. EL course delivery\r\n4. Supporting resource banks \r\n\r\n', '2018-02-13 01:00:11', 'upload/attachment/c77c66f6d25086ce85123bc0a5d30d65.docx', '<p>welldone</p>', NULL, '2018-02-13 07:00:11', 'F'),
