(141, 98, 'Differentiate teaching from instruction using suitable examples. Prepare an instructional text for your students following the rules of instructional design theory (your own discipline).', 'Module: 2 Instructional design\r\nUnit: IMD1 Principles of Instructional design and typography\r\nFellow ID: 181020\r\nAssignment No: 1\r\nDifferentiate teaching from instruction using suitable examples. Prepare an instructional text for your students following the rules of instructional design theory (your own discipline).\r\n\r\nTeaching is the process of attending to people''s needs, experiences and feelings, and making specific interventions to help them learn particular things. It is the imparting of knowledge by a teacher or other knowledgeable person.\r\nInstruction is vital for education, as it is the transfer of learning from one person to another. Any time we are given directions or told how to do something we are receiving instruction.\r\nThe noun instruction is related to the word structure. Effective instruction is presented in an orderly, structured manner.\r\nTeaching and learning usually involve instruction. Teachers have to come up with varied instructional materials and must use the right strategies in teaching their lessons. \r\n\r\n         Differentiation between teaching and instruction are given below:\r\n We can teach almost anything: concepts, ideas, theories but when we instruct someone, we are giving them a set of tools or tasks to do something specific.\r\n Teaching works for overall development while specific instruction works for specific domain development. \r\nFor example-\r\n In heat coagulation test, the instructions are-\r\n• Objective- it is done to detect protein in urine\r\n• Materials and method\r\n• Comments\r\nBut from the point of view of teaching, we can say many things about heat coagulation test other than instruction. Suppose, we can define and classify proteinuria, mention other methods of detection of protein in urine, explain the changes happen to protein after heat coagulation test and many more things.\r\n Teaching is bi-directional but instruction is uni-directional. For example, teachers form their lesson plan on a topic according to instruction but when they apply this lesson plan in class it becomes teaching and they get learner’s response\r\n Teaching is more complex in nature. When we talk about teaching, we are dealing with different techniques, strategies, and approaches that will facilitate learning. \r\nInstruction, is not as complex as teaching. Instruction makes the teaching easy. Instruction is simply giving direction. We instruct someone on what to do and how to do it. \r\nFor instance, in medical college students are given instructions by their teachers on how to answer a test or how to perform an experiment. \r\n Teaching is also a never ending process. We don''t only learn from teachers but also from those around us. This makes teaching both formal and informal. It is formal when it occurs inside the classroom or informal when you learn things outside the portals of the educational institute.\r\nIn educational environment, Instruction is always formal and given by the teacher or facilitator by various ways like lecture notes, handouts, power point, overhead projector etc.\r\nIn teaching, Instructions must be understood and followed strictly in order to accomplish a particular task. Once we fail to do so, we won''t be able to finish the task correctly. \r\nTeaching and instruction go together especially in education. Both are needed in helping people learn and develop as individual.\r\n\r\nI am from Biochemistry discipline and my instructional text for my students following the rules of instructional design theory are given below:\r\n\r\nTopic: Concept of Digestion and Absorption of Carbohydrate\r\nIntroduction:\r\nGain attention \r\nTo gain attention, I raise questions like,\r\n To get energy what we intake? (We intake carbohydrate. It is ingested in complex form) \r\n  Can they tell the name of the process that makes this complex carbohydrate in simpler form after ingestion and make it suitable for absorption? (It is digestion)\r\nInform the learning objectives\r\nAt the end of the session the students will be able to:\r\n1. Name the dietary carbohydrates\r\n2. State the names and sources of enzymes of carbohydrate digestion\r\n3. Describe the steps of carbohydrate digestion with the name of end products\r\n4. Enumerate the Process of carbohydrate absorption\r\n\r\nStimulating recall pre-requisite knowledge\r\nIn their undergraduate level and from my previous lectures students have already known about the carbohydrate. So, I ask them-\r\n Can they name the dietary carbohydrates?\r\n What types of carbohydrates they are?\r\n Can they say from where carbohydrate digestion starts?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nContent\r\n\r\nPresent new content\r\n1. Mention the main dietary carbohydrates\r\n2. Name the enzymes that are required for carbohydrate digestion\r\n3. Show a figure (by power point presentation) of Gastro intestinal tract to illustrate-\r\na. Sites of carbohydrate digestion\r\nb. Location of enzymes\r\n4. Discuss the steps of digestion (by power point presentation)\r\n5. Name the end products of carbohydrate digestion\r\n6. Enumerate the different processes of absorption of \r\ncarbohydrate \r\n7. Explain “Lactose intolerance”\r\n\r\n Provide guidance\r\n Advise to go through the text book “Lippincott’s Biochemistry, 7th edition, page # 86 to 89 along with lectures\r\n Provide this URL to see the video of carbohydrate digestion and absorption https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LWfXeCVp7Wk\r\n Provide the hand out of pictures of carbohydrate digestion and absorption\r\n\r\nAssessment\r\n\r\nEliciting the performance\r\nBy asking random questions to the students about the topic\r\n\r\nProviding feedback on performance\r\nIf the student answer correctly, I appreciate him or\r\nIf the student can’t answer correctly I ask him related questions to reach the correct answer.\r\nIf he fails to answer, I collect answer from another student and inform the 1st student to listen the lecture more carefully and discuss the topics with his classmates after the class.\r\n\r\nAssessing the performance\r\nTo assess the student’s performance, I provide 3 MCQs, each has 5 stems on topic in power point presentation and ask them to write only “True or False” in a paper with their roll number. \r\n\r\nSummary\r\n\r\nEnhance retention and transfer\r\n Summarize the topic in short to enhance retention \r\n Ask them whether they have any questions about the topic\r\n \r\n                  \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFigure of carbohydrate digestion  \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFigure of glucose absorption\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '2018-02-23 09:05:01', 'upload/attachment/be890270006c015a9d82ae52e6deed48.doc', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
